    dc:date "2005" ;
    dc:title "Terrestrial planarians (Platyhelminthes, with three new species) and nemertines of Bermuda" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048560>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048562> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048560>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–5. Amaga expatria n. sp. Holotype. 1. Whole worm, preserved. The two dotted oval outlines indicate the positions of the pharynx and copulatory apparatus. Regions removed for transverse (ts) and longitudinal (ls) sectioning are indicated by dashed lines. Length approximately 80 mm. 2–4. Eye distribution traced from cleared specimen. Scale lines 1 mm. 2. Lateral view of left side of anterior end. 3. Dorsal view of right side about a quarter of the way from the anterior end. 4. Dorsal view of right side adjacent to the pharynx. Dashed line in 3 & 4 represents the mid­line. 5. Transverse section anterior to the pharynx. Scale line 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5048560/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048562>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6–8. Amaga expatria n. sp. Holotype. 6. Diagram of the copulatory apparatus reconstructed from longitudinal sections (cf. Fig. 7). Anterior is to the left. Scale line 1 mm. 7. Montage of micrographs of longitudinal sections through the copulatory apparatus (cf. Fig. 6). Anterior is to the left. Scale line 1 mm. 8. Section, lateral to that of Fig. 7, through the posterior part of vagina showing the relationship of the ovo­vitelline ducts and vagina. Same scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5048562/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

